==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''nimietās'', from ''nimius'' 'excessive' and ''nimis'' 'excessively'
===Noun===
# state of being in excess, possessing more than is needed
====quotations====
''There is a nimiety, a too-muchness to all Germans.'' -- Samuel Taylor Coleridge
====synonyms====
[[superfluity]]
[[surfeit]]
